id: pm-izx5
title: Document schema/fields.json runtime custom field authoring in CONFIGURATION.md
description: "CONFIGURATION.md has zero mention of schema/fields.json, RuntimeFieldDefinition, or how to author custom runtime fields. The schema section (schema/types.json and schema/statuses.json) is documented, but schema/fields.json is the most powerful customization primitive (adds typed flags to create/update/list) and is completely undocumented."
type: Chore
status: open
priority: 3
tags[3]: "area:docs","area:schema",dx
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:08:57.246Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-07T10:15:55.017Z"
author: audit-cli-schema-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- CONFIGURATION.md adds a 'Custom Runtime Fields' section covering:\n- schema/fields.json file path and shape ({ \"fields\": [RuntimeFieldDefinition...] })\n- All RuntimeFieldDefinition properties with examples\n- One end-to-end example (add a 'component' string field on Task items)\n- Note on unknown_field_policy for governance\n- Note that pm schema add-field (once implemented) is the preferred CLI method\n- COMMANDS.md schema section cross-references custom fields"
parent: pm-8jdc
risk: low
confidence: high
body: "## Context\n\nCONFIGURATION.md:\n- Documents schema/types.json (custom types) and schema/statuses.json (custom statuses)\n- Has no mention of schema/fields.json, RuntimeFieldDefinition, or custom field authoring\n\nThe fields system (src/core/schema/runtime-schema.ts:238-278 normalizeRuntimeFieldDefinition) supports:\n- key, type (string/number/boolean/string_array), metadata_key, cli_flag, cli_aliases\n- commands (which commands show the flag: create/update/list/search/context)\n- required, required_on_create, allow_unset\n- required_types (only required for certain item types)\n- description (shown in --help)\n\ndocs/CONFIGURATION.md:71 does list schema.type_workflows[] with a JSON example. The same pattern should be followed for a fields.json example.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- CONFIGURATION.md adds a 'Custom Runtime Fields' section covering:\n  - schema/fields.json file path and shape ({ \"fields\": [RuntimeFieldDefinition...] })\n  - All RuntimeFieldDefinition properties with examples\n  - One end-to-end example (add a 'component' string field on Task items)\n  - Note on unknown_field_policy for governance\n  - Note that pm schema add-field (once implemented) is the preferred CLI method\n- COMMANDS.md schema section cross-references custom fields\n\n## Evidence\n\n- docs/CONFIGURATION.md (full file — no fields.json mention)\n- src/core/schema/runtime-schema.ts:238-278 (RuntimeFieldDefinition shape)\n- src/core/schema/runtime-schema.ts:28 (DEFAULT_RUNTIME_SCHEMA_FILE_PATHS.fields = 'schema/fields.json')\n- docs/CONFIGURATION.md:71 (type_workflows example — style to follow)"
